  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The descendants of Salma: Bethlehem, i.e., the family of Bethlehem (see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 2:52",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), the Netophathites, i.e., the inhabitants of the town of Netophah, which, according to our verse and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and especially ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nehemiah 7:26",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is to be looked for in the neighbourhood of Bethlehem (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 9:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "); a family which produced at various times renowned men (cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 23:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 25:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezra 2:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The following words, י עטחרות ב, i.e., \"crowns of the house of Joab,\" can only be the name of a place which is mentioned instead of its inhabitants; for עטרות occurs elsewhere, sometimes alone, and sometimes in conjunction with a proper name, as the name of places: cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 32:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 16:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 16:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 16:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Joshua 18:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Hazi-Hammanahath is certainly to be sought in the neighbourhood of Manahath, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 8:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", whose position has, however, not yet been ascertained. הצּרעי is only another form of הצּרעתי, and is derived from the masculine of the word. The Zorites here spoken of formed a second division of the inhabitants of Zoreah and the neighbourhood, along with the Zoreathites descended from Shobal, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 2:53",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  }
